    <string name="question_lion">Why do lions have manes?</string>
    <string name="answer_lion_protection">The mane protects the neck during fights against other males.</string>
    <string name="answer_lion_fitness">The mane serves signals about the lion\'s fitness. Darker and bigger manes are more attractive for lionesses</string>
    <string name="answer_lion_temperature">The mane\'s size depends on the environmental temperature and it\'s used to control the body temperature of the male lion.</string>
    <string name="answer_lion_fighting">The mane signals information to other males about the fighting abilities.</string>
    <string name="question_hummingbird">How do hummingbirds fly backwards?</string>
    <string name="answer_hummingbird_helicopter">Hummingbirds move their wings like a helicopter.</string>
    <string name="answer_hummingbird_myth">This is a myth. Hummingbirds cannot fly backwards.</string>
    <string name="answer_hummingbird_eight_beat">Hummingbirds rotate their wings during the for- and backward wing beat.</string>
    <string name="answer_hummingbird_speed">The high beat frequency of the wings allows the hummingbirds to fly backwards.</string>
