    <string name="question_elephant">Why do elephants have big ears?</string>
    <string name="answer_elephant_communication">They use only their ears to communicate over larger distances. Bigger ears can be better seen.</string>
    <string name="answer_elephant_hearing">Because of the big ears, elephants can hear a broader frequency spectrum of tones.</string>
    <string name="answer_elephant_attractive">Bigger ears are more attractive to other elephants, because it indicates a greater fitness.</string>
    <string name="answer_elephant_temperature">The ears are used to regulate the body temperature. The heat loss can be raised by flapping.</string>
    <string name="question_tiger">Why are tigers black and reddish-orange striped?</string>
    <string name="answer_tiger_protection">The stripes confuse mosquitos, which transmit diseases.</string>
    <string name="answer_tiger_camouflage">Tigers live in jungles and long grass, so the stripes help to blend into the surroundings.</string>
    <string name="answer_tiger_sight">Most of the tiger\'s prey do not see colors. The orange and black shaded fur may look like shadows for those animals.</string>
    <string name="answer_tiger_temperature">The black and orange stripes generate a temperature gradient, which leads to air stream. This regulates the body temperature.</string>
